def: One of several upright slender calcareous processes whichsurround the central part of the calicle of certain corals.

One who, or that which, has an appetite for human flesh;specifically, one of certain large sharks (esp. CarcharodonRondeleti); also, a lion or a tiger which has acquired the habit offeeding upon human flesh.
Befitting or indicating a coxcomb; like a coxcomb; foppish;conceited.-- Cox*comb"ic*al*ly, adv.Studded all over in coxcombical fashion with little brass nails. W.Irving.

A nutritious article of food, much used in Scotland, made fromthe husk of the oat by a process not unlike that by which commonstarch is made; -- called flummery in England. [Written also sowans,and sowins.]
Of or pertaining to Poland or its inhabitants.-- n.

An empirical system which assumes that the human body iscomposed of four elements, earth, air, fire, and water, and thatvegetable medicines alone should be used; -- from the founder, Dr.Samuel Thomson, of Massachusetts.
The quality or state of being human.
Formation and separation of lamin√¶ or layers; one of themethods by which the various blastodermic layers of the ovum aredifferentiated.
An initial sound, as of a word or syllable.
